snippet.textDisplay:
To me, the most surprising result was the brake test; but then was the Porsche equipped with the very best brake they "offer"? Tesla offers better brakes from the start with the Model 3 Performance compared to a "regular" Model 3.


As to the drag races, I was not really surprised given the power to weight ratios of both cars. Yes, electric cars do have a much better powerband at "low" speeds, but the gearboxes on ICE cars are not only necessary, but advantageous at "high" speeds: they just produce more power. When the gear is right, of course. And yes, "low" and "high" in quotes because frankly, on the road, you drive at "low" speeds unless you're a lunatic.


All in all, in day to day driving, should money not be an object, Tesla every day.
